Senate Resolution 348
By: Senator Moore of the 53rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life of Trooper William Frederick Black, Jr., and dedicating an intersection in
2 his memory; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, our nation's security continues to rely on patriotic men and women who put
4 their personal lives on hold in order to place themselves in harm's way to protect the
5 freedoms that all United States citizens cherish; and
6 WHEREAS, Trooper William Frederick Black, Jr., was a standout football player for Lanier
7 High School, where he led the Poets to a state championship; and
8 WHEREAS, he went on to study aeronautical engineering at Auburn University, where he
9 played basketball and football; and
10 WHEREAS, Trooper Black served as a guardian of this nation's freedom and liberty with the
11 United States Army Reserves and graduated among the first class of troopers in Georgia,
12 with a badge number of 8; and
