13 WHEREAS, while patrolling on Georgia Highway 41 near Ringgold, Georgia, Trooper
14 Black's life was tragically cut short in the line of duty when he was shot during a traffic stop;
15 and
16 WHEREAS, Trooper Black embodied the spirit of service and willingness to find meaning
17 in something greater than himself, and it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable
18 and distinguished Georgian be recognized appropriately by dedicating an intersection in his
19 memory.
20 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED AND ENACTED BY THE GENERAL
21 ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA that the intersection of State Route 3 and Roach Hollow Road
22 in Catoosa County is dedicated as the Trooper William Black, Jr. Memorial Intersection.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Transportation is authorized and
24 directed to erect and maintain appropriate signs dedicating the Trooper William Black, Jr.
25 Memorial Intersection.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
27 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the family of
28 Trooper William Frederick Black, Jr., and to the Department of Transportation.
